    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble meets all quantitative acceptance criteria for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the strong output comparison results across two independent laboratories and the medium model risk level. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Aleatory uncertainty contributions from material variability, assembly torque, and inter-laboratory differences are acknowledged in the assessment narrative; formal quantification artifacts are linked for the stiffness result only, with yield force and force-at-40mm results relying on qualitative characterization.",
